Sentencas: Nickel solid oxide fuel cell anodes are unsuitable for operation with dry natural gas because of carbon deposition.
Titulo: EVALUATION OF PEROVSKITE ANODES FOR THE COMPLETE OXIDATION OF DRY METHANE IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: Results from steady state and temperature programmed experiments over an alternative anode material, La0.8Ca0.2CrO3-x, indicate that both complete oxidation of methane and surface methane dissociation occur at temperatures above 500 degrees C. Negligible carbon deposition occurs during complete oxidation.
Titulo: EVALUATION OF PEROVSKITE ANODES FOR THE COMPLETE OXIDATION OF DRY METHANE IN SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS
